<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 16 at 11:55AM MST  by NWS Missoula</headline>
<description>...Intense snow showers will impact portions of northeastern Deer
Lodge, east central Granite, Silver Bow and south central Powell
Counties through 100 PM MST...
At 1154 AM MST, trained weather spotters reported intense snow
showers along a line extending from near Warm Springs to 7 miles west
of Silver Star. Movement was northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Visibility one-half mile or less.
SOURCE...Trained weather spotters.
IMPACT...Low visibility could result in dangerous driving
conditions.
Locations impacted include...
Butte, Anaconda, Silver Bow, Walkerville, Warm Springs, Galen,
Gregson Hot Springs, Nissler, Crackerville, Racetrack, Lost Creek,
Opportunity, Ramsay, Janney and Newcomb.
This includes Interstate 90 between mile markers 188 and 231.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
